<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="989" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d989">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3087a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Minister to
                                    Cuba</gloss>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d989fn1">Same to all Latin-American
                                missions.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-20T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>After the words “but merely,” last sentence first paragraph, of
                            Department’s March 6, 7 p.m., insert the words “to prevent smuggling and
                            any other infractions of our so-called neutrality statutes and.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>